{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":5,"timestamp":1772226133,"nonce":"Ge7VKMVesgJZxRJ0Unl+AIaIjyk=","metadata":{"github-id":"LE_lADOQ241x87ulqyYzwAAAAVjqaJ9"},"added":["bug"],"removed":[]},{"type":5,"timestamp":1772226133,"nonce":"V7KXu3TsIMQ7zdaddV6Cu2uuVvE=","metadata":{"github-id":"LE_lADOQ241x87ulqyYzwAAAAVjqaKu"},"added":["enhancement"],"removed":[]},{"type":3,"timestamp":1772226428,"nonce":"VItiZnv8hJa5tdG4YfPu11TzB5A=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOQ241x87s7x9i","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/318#issuecomment-3975094114"},"message":"Summaries should live in the project repo and yes, --skill worktree exception should work for layers as well.","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1772226539,"nonce":"DtF/2KMHWeHKCIij0UUDh797iyQ=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOQ241x87s7zyI","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/318#issuecomment-3975101576"},"message":"## Review\n\n### Scope Assessment\n\n**Well-scoped?** Yes — the issue identifies a specific inconsistency across 4 files with 3 clear questions. The fix is small: update `worktree_create.sh` to support `--skill` with `--type layer`, update the skill docs, and reconcile references. Single-PR scope.\n\n**Right repo?** Yes — all affected files (`worktree_create.sh`, `SKILL.md`, the template) live in the workspace repo.\n\n**Dependencies**: The owner's [comment](https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/318#issuecomment-3975094114) resolves the design questions (summaries in project repo; `--skill` should support layers). No other blocking issues.\n\n### Principle Alignment\n\n| Principle | Status | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| Workspace vs. project separation | **Action needed** | This is the core issue. ADR-0003 is explicit: project-specific knowledge lives in the manifest repo via `.agents/workspace-context/`, not the workspace repo. The current skill + `--skill --type workspace` combination would put summaries in the wrong repo. Owner's comment confirms: fix to target the project repo. |\n| Enforcement over documentation | **Watch** | The `--skill` flag currently only works with `--type workspace` — that's an enforcement gap since it silently allows the wrong workflow. The fix should either extend `--skill` to support `--type layer` or error clearly if misused. |\n| A change includes its consequences | **Watch** | Consequences map: changing worktree scripts requires updating `.agent/WORKTREE_GUIDE.md` and the `AGENTS.md` worktree section. The `--skill` examples in both docs currently only show `--type workspace`. |\n| Only what's needed | OK | Small, targeted fix. |\n| Improve incrementally | OK | Fixing one inconsistency before the first real use. |\n\n### ADR Applicability\n\n| ADR | Triggered | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| 0002 — Worktree isolation | Yes | Extending worktree script capabilities. The ADR's spirit (isolation via worktrees) is maintained — this just adds `--type layer` support for skill worktrees. |\n| 0003 — Project-agnostic workspace | Yes | This is the ADR that reveals the bug. Project knowledge belongs in the manifest repo, not the workspace. The fix aligns the skill with this ADR. |\n| 0005 — Layered enforcement | No | Not adding new enforcement rules. |\n\n### Consequences\n\nPer the consequences map, when changing worktree scripts also update:\n- `.agent/WORKTREE_GUIDE.md` — skill worktree examples (currently only show workspace type)\n- `AGENTS.md` — skill worktree exception section (currently says `--type workspace` implicitly)\n- `.agent/templates/knowledge_update_issue.md` — may need to show the `--skill` workflow as an alternative to the issue-based workflow\n- `worktree_enter.sh` / `worktree_remove.sh` — verify they handle skill+layer worktrees correctly\n\n### Recommendations\n\n- The `--skill` + `--type layer` combination will need `--layer` and `--packages` parameters too. Decide whether these should be required flags or whether the skill can infer a default (e.g., always targeting the manifest repo).\n- Consider whether the `gather-project-knowledge` entry should stay in `ALLOWED_SKILLS` at all, or whether using a normal issue-based layer worktree (per the knowledge update template) is simpler and sufficient. The `--skill` exception exists to avoid needing a GitHub issue for recurring updates — but if the overhead of one issue per refresh is acceptable, the simpler path avoids the complexity of extending `--skill` to layers.\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1772227365,"nonce":"HWPGex06zjaaer2SIIlrpc9yEww=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOQ241x87s8ACn","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/318#issuecomment-3975151783"},"message":"## Design Decisions\n\nBased on brainstorming discussion, here are the resolved decisions:\n\n### 1. Require an issue instead of `--skill` exception\n\nDrop `gather-project-knowledge` from the `ALLOWED_SKILLS` list in `worktree_create.sh`. Use a normal `--issue` + `--type layer` worktree targeting the repo where summaries should be written. The existing knowledge update issue template already describes this workflow.\n\n**Rationale**: The `--skill` exception only supports `--type workspace`, but this skill writes to a project repo. Extending `--skill` to support layers adds complexity to three scripts to avoid creating one GitHub issue. The issue also provides an audit trail for what triggered each refresh.\n\n### 2. Two modes: manifest repo vs. non-manifest repo\n\n- **Run on the manifest repo** (e.g., `unh_marine_autonomy`): Scans all workspace repos across all layers. Writes the full set of summaries (`workspace_overview.md`, `governance_summary.md`, `project_profiles/\u003crepo\u003e.md`) to `.agents/workspace-context/`. This is the primary use case — the workspace symlink (`.agent/project_knowledge/`) points here.\n\n- **Run on any non-manifest repo** (e.g., `camp`, `udp_bridge`): Generates a self-profile only, written to its own `.agents/workspace-context/`. Useful for bootstrapping a repo's `.agents/` directory independently.\n\n### 3. No recursion\n\nIf a scanned repo already has `.agents/workspace-context/`, read it as input (summarize/incorporate), don't re-scan through it. A sub-project manifest's own summaries become input to the workspace-level aggregation.\n\n### Scope of Changes\n\n- `worktree_create.sh` — remove `gather-project-knowledge` from `ALLOWED_SKILLS`\n- `.claude/skills/gather-project-knowledge/SKILL.md` — update prerequisites, add manifest vs. non-manifest mode docs\n- `.agent/WORKTREE_GUIDE.md` — update skill worktree section (only `research` uses the exception now)\n- `AGENTS.md` — update skill worktree allowlist reference\n- `.agent/templates/knowledge_update_issue.md` — minor updates if needed\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1772228529,"nonce":"+z0nw8x1LRZecXGg2dnFV2C5MmA=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOQ241x87s8SBo","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/318#issuecomment-3975225448"},"message":"Note: The **research** skill has the same issue for its `--scope project` workflow.\n\n- `SKILL.md` line 84 creates a `--type workspace` worktree\n- But the project digest (line 45-46) lives in the **manifest repo** at `.agents/workspace-context/research_digest.md`\n- So `/research --scope project \u003ctopic\u003e` would be in a workspace worktree but needing to commit to a project repo — same mismatch\n\nThe workspace-scoped path (`/research \u003ctopic\u003e`) is unaffected since `.agent/knowledge/research_digest.md` is in the workspace repo.\n\nWhatever fix is chosen for `gather-project-knowledge` should also be applied to the research skill.\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null},{"type":4,"timestamp":1772229704,"nonce":"GAWKP6SwUTcfNZEWavyL1+V76vc=","metadata":{"github-id":"CE_lADOQ241x87ulqyYzwAAAAVjvVhV"},"status":2}]}